<div id="review_23041280" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/23041280" />
    <a title="Kara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/708116-kara"><img alt="Kara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1198348655p2/708116.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/23041280?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kara" href="/user/show/708116-kara">Kara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/708116-kara?shelf=science-nature">science-nature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/708116-kara?shelf=memoir">memoir</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer23041280" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12021999500674781365">FIVE STARS AND BEYOND! This memoir chronicles, in the form of a daily log, the months-long trek Matthiessen took in the Himalaya with legendary wildlife biologist George Schaller. GS had planned the expedition to observe montane wildlife - primarily the snow leopard and its prey, the blue sheep. PM, a student of Buddhism, made the journey as a kind of pilgrimage after the death of his wife. Their ultimate destination was a range so remote it was nearly impenetrable by travelers and its villages </span>
  <span id="freeText12021999500674781365" style="display:none">FIVE STARS AND BEYOND! This memoir chronicles, in the form of a daily log, the months-long trek Matthiessen took in the Himalaya with legendary wildlife biologist George Schaller. GS had planned the expedition to observe montane wildlife - primarily the snow leopard and its prey, the blue sheep. PM, a student of Buddhism, made the journey as a kind of pilgrimage after the death of his wife. Their ultimate destination was a range so remote it was nearly impenetrable by travelers and its villages seemed lost in time. The setting and objectives of this expedition were so extraordinary its story could hardly fail to be interesting. But Matthiessen's observations of both his inner and outer worlds are *astonishing* in their simplicity and clarity. The plain beauty and truth in his prose totally floored me again and again. Like scripture, this book should be published in a hardbound pocket-sized edition; right now I want to keep it with me at all times. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12021999500674781365" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review23041280">
  <td colspan="2">
